<h4>Installation</h4>


<b>Now</b> you can try ChronoJump&nbsp;<b>0.3</b> from any PC.
	<p>
	<h5>GNU/Linux</h5>
	<ol>
		<li>Install Mono. 
		<li>Download: <a href="https://software-libre.org/project/showfiles.php?group_id=63&release_id=148">chronojump-monolive-03.tgz</a>
	</ol>

	<h5>Windows</h5>
	<ul>
		<li>Read this e-mail (spanish): <a href="http://lists.software-libre.org/pipermail/chronojump-general_es/2005-September/000066.html">Chronojump-mono-live-cd 0.3 . Versión deChronojump fácil de usar para usuarios Windows</a>
	</ul>
	<p>
	<h5>CVS</h5>
	<ul>
		<li>If you are an <b>advanced&nbsp;user</b>: from an operative system GNU/Linux, install <a href="http://www.mono-project.com">Mono</a> and download the Chronojump sources on the CVS:
		<ol>
			<li><tt>cvs - d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.software-libre.org:/cvsroot/chronojump login</tt> (when the password is requested press 'enter').
			<li><tt>cvs - z3 - d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.software-libre.org:/cvsroot/chronojump co chronojump</tt>
			<li>Execute <tt>/chronojump.exe</tt> or compile with <tt>make</tt>.
		</ol>
	</ul>
	
<p>
Help can be found subscribing to the <a href="contact.html">mailing lists</a>.
<p> 
If you wish to know the advance of the project, please check on <a href="http://cvs.software-libre.org/cgi-bin/cvsweb.cgi/chronojump/changelog.txt?cvsroot=chronojump">changelog&nbsp;file</a> (click the number at the right hand corner of "Revision"), and the <a href="http://lists.software-libre.org/pipermail/chronojump-developers/">chronojump developers mailing list archives</a>.


